doc.ContractDescription: A PROGRAM IS PROPOSED TO DEVELOP A TOOL TO DETERMINE THE NATURE OF SOLAR WIND PLASMA ENTRY INTO THE EARTHS MAGNETOSPHERE. A MODEL WILL BE CREATED TO PREDICT LINE OF SIGHT PROJECTIONS OF DIFFERENT ION DISPERSION STRUCTURES IN THE CUSPS. ION DISPERSIONS AND PLASMA ENTRY ARE THE DIRECT RESULT MAGNETOPAUSE RECONNECTION. STRUCTURED ION DISPERSIONS GIVE INFORMATION DESCRIBING THE MACROSCALE PROPERTIES OF RECONNECTION AT THE MAGNETOPAUSE. FUTURE MEASUREMENTS FROM THE NASA SPONSORED DXLII SOUNDING ROCKET MAY BE ABLE TO PROVIDE SUCH A WIDE FIELD OF VIEW MEASUREMENTS OF THE CUSP DISPERSIONS IN THE NEAR FUTURE. DEVELOPMENT OF A NUMERICAL MODEL NOW WILL ENABLE PROPER INTERPRETATION AND MAXIMIZE THE BENEFIT TO THIS AND OTHER NASA MISSIONS. IT CAN BE DIFFICULT TO DETERMINE THE GLOBAL NATURE OF MAGNETOPAUSE RECONNECTION FROM ISOLATED INSITU SPACECRAFT MEASUREMENTS. EVEN CLUSTERS OF SPACECRAFT WITH INTERSPACECRAFT SEPARATIONS RANGING FROM 10S OF KILOMETERS MMS OR EVEN 1 2 RE CLUSTER CANNOT DETERMINE THE EXTENT AND THEREFORE SIGNIFICANCE OF PROCESSES THAT MAY SPAN 10S OF RE. THE MAGNETIC FIELD LINES ON WHICH RECONNECTION OCCURS CONVERGE IN THE CUSPS, WHERE OBSERVATIONS OF CUSP ION DISPERSIONS PROVIDE A RICH SOURCE OF INFORMATION ON THE CHARACTERISTICS OF RECONNECTION. INHERENT AMBIGUITY BETWEEN SPATIAL AND TEMPORAL FEATURES IN INSITU MEASUREMENTS HINDERS OUR ABILITY TO INTERPRET THESE OBSERVATIONS. IMAGING, SUCH AS THAT TO BE UNDERTAKEN BY DXLII, AND PROPER DECONVOLUTION OF THE SIGNAL WILL ALLOW FOR A MACROSCALE UNDERSTANDING OF THE PROPERTIES OF RECONNECTION. MAGNETOPAUSE RECONNECTION IS THE PRIMARY MECHANISM THROUGH WHICH ENERGY IS DEPOSITED INTO THE MAGNETOPAUSE TO FUEL GEOMAGNETIC STORMS. THE PROJECT THUS HAS GREAT RELEVANCE FOR A NUMBER OF ACTIVE NASA MISSIONS SUCH AS THEMIS, VAN ALLEN PROBES, AND MMS. THIS PROJECT IS ALSO INLINE WITH GOAL 2 OF THE NRC DECADAL SURVEY FOR SOLAR AND SPACE PHYSICS TO DETERMINE THE DYNAMICS AND COUPLING OF EARTHS MAGNETOSPHERE, IONOSPHERE, AND ATMOSPHERE AND THEIR RESPONSE TO SOLAR AND TERRESTRIAL INPUTS.
